               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 3ra-122vb)&#xD; -
                     Introduction (fols. 3ra-5rb)&#xD; - Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols.
                     9va-16vb)&#xD; - Maṣḥaf za-wäḍʾat ʾǝm-ʾIyarusalem “Book that Came from
                     Jerusalem” (fols. 17ra-22ra)&#xD; - Homily by St Jacob of Serug for the funeral
                     of priests and deacons (fols. 65va-68ra)&#xD; - Homily by ʾabbā Salāmā,
                     Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols. 80ra-83va)&#xD; - Lǝfāfa ṣǝdq “Bandlet of
                     Righteousness” (fols. 85vb-88vb)&#xD; - Mangada samāy “Journey to Heaven”
                     (fols. 88vb-89va)&#xD; - Antiphons (ʾaryām, kǝśtat, salām, mazmur) (fols.
                     28ra-29ra, 43vb-44vb, 48ra-va, 49va-51ra, 53rb, 55ra-56ra, 57ra, 58va-59ra,
                     61rb-va, 64vb)&#xD; II) Ṣalota śǝryätä ḫaṭiʾat “Prayer of Absolution of Sins”
                     (fols. 123ra-126rb), (cp. EMML 427(9))&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-2.</summary>
